Together with the Bulgarian trumpeter Miroslav Petkov he gives a concert under the motto "Black Sea meets Black Forest", or also "Balkanfolklore" meets a classical German education with roots in brass music.
Both soloists are winners and winners of numerous international competitions and hold solo positions in top European orchestras.
Petkov is a solo trumpeter with the renowned Concertgebouw Orchestra Amsterdam and Frederic Belli is a solo tromponist of the SWR Symphony Orchestra.
Both combine the desire not only to cross the borders on their instruments, but also to merge the borders of the different genres.
Thus Johann Sebastian Bach resounds with the two as in a new robe, Daniel Schnyder's "world music" unites with Bulgarian folklore, and in the play "Exchange Suite" by jazz echo prize winner Nils Wogram, classical music, jazz and free play merge into a fascinating overall work of art.
This core piece of the programme was only premiered this spring with huge success in Freiburg.
