Coe praises "honest" Russian apology for doping scandal
The world-wide head of athletics, Sebastian Coe, praised Thursday, which he described as an obvious excuse from Russia to a doping scandal, but he repeated that it was not the moment for the country to be re-entered into sport.
Russia's athletics chief Dmitry Shylakhtin said during the IAAF Congress on the eve of the World Athletics Championships that his country's banishment from sport was correct and that he was determined to fight doping.
He said he was sorry for "all athletes who got gold and silver medals taken away in competitions".
