This repetition of the story is simultaneously nostalgic because of the glorious days of the characters of the 80's, for the 90's grunge era (when thinkers David Wain and Michael Showalter shot the sketch comedy "The State" for MTV), and for themselves - that is, for 2001, before their stars, such as Elizabeth Banks, Amy Poehler and Paul Rudd, went to bigger things.
