Since Guzman's arrest last year and extradition to the United States in January, Sinaloa had become one of the country's bloodiest battlefields as rival factions struggle here to fill the vacuum.
It doesn't matter that in Sinaloa every day someone or several people are shot in the street or that the cemetery is full of decorated, two-story mausoleums for drug kings who are larger than many homes for the living.
