Roll backwards: the city hires 46 kitchen aids
The city organizes the day care table itself.
With fixed contacts for the children and an assignment to the team.
In the city day care centres the clock is turned back.
On 1 September, the city of Krefeld will take over the food supply in the urban day care facilities (kitas) in its own right.
For Sonja Pommeranz, deputy head of the youth aid department, this is good news: "We were all very happy".
A caterer takes over this task and supplies freshly cooked chilled food.
The city operates 46 day care centres in the Krefeld area, and in 44, the children get a warm meal at lunchtime.
In the last daycare year, 2800 children sat at the tables, and the demand is growing steadily.
"In the meantime, not only children who are looked after for 45 hours a week are eating lunch in the day care center," explains Pommeranz.
"The offer is also valid in 35-hour care if children stay until 2 p.m.".
From 1 September, 46 part-time workers will be in the kitchen service: they will heat the food provided, add salad, raw food and fruit, portion the meal individually, spend the food, clear, rinse and clean the kitchen.
"Employees are firmly assigned to a daycare centre," says Pommeranz.
The size - there are two groups as well as seven groups - determines the number of hours.
"The kitchen helpers are now firmly part of the Kita team," says Pommeranz, satisfied.
"So they are much more closely involved and it is easier for the daycare management to implement educational concepts".
This is also what it is about: healthy nutrition and cooking lessons.
"The children should help prepare the food".
The direct connection of the Küchenkraft to the team makes sense.
Also for the children.
"They have a known power in daycare, a person familiar to them, and not constantly changing people".
This continuity is important for the children.
The cleaning of the nursery rooms - so far also the task of the kitchen workers - will be done by special cleaning staff in the future.
This variant - the separation of cleaning and kitchen service - has besides the quality improvement of the kitchen performance also the charm that it has proved to be the most economical in the cost comparison between self-directing and foreign procurement for the city, it is said from the press office.
And that despite the fact that 46 part-time workers are being recruited.
"But these hours are not so important for around 750 people in the education sector," says Sonja Pommeranz.
Afghan democracy depends on the political role of women, says the UN
Elections can only be representative if all members of society, including women, play a role, said the head of the UN mission in Afghanistan on Wednesday.
Nicholas Haysom, acting head of the United Nations mission, said hundreds of women will run in the council elections in the provinces. Three women are running for the role of vice president and more than 30 percent of newly registered voters are women.
"The role of women cannot be overestimated," he said in a statement on Wednesday.
Elections can only be truly representative and credible if women participate fully and are involved in all parts of the electoral process.
Afghan elections for the provincial council and presidential elections will take place on 5 April.
The Taliban have published threats against an electoral process that coincide with the transition from international combat to an advisory role.
This year, for the first time, the elections will hand over power peacefully from one democratically elected government to the next.
Haysom said a strong role for women will further strengthen Afghanistan's democratic success.
The Afghan Independent Electoral Commission reports that 1.2 million women are registered by a total of 3.6 million registered voters.
